{"id":44,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":44,"title":"Chapter 41: The Signs of Christ’s Birth","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 41"],["h1","The Signs of Christ’s Birth"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p3"},"Nephi, the son of Helaman, gave the sacred records and scriptures to his oldest son, Nephi."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.2"},"3 Nephi 1:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p5"},"The Nephites saw great signs and miracles that prophets had said would happen before Jesus Christ’s birth."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.4"},"3 Nephi 1:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p7"},"But some Nephites said the time for Jesus’ birth had already passed. They mocked those who still believed Samuel the Lamanite’s prophecies."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.5-6"},"3 Nephi 1:5–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p9"},"The people who believed in Jesus Christ and in the prophets were sad to think that something might keep the prophecies from being fulfilled."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.7"},"3 Nephi 1:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p11"},"The people watched faithfully for a night with no darkness, which was the sign that Jesus Christ would be born."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.8"},"3 Nephi 1:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p13"},"Those who did not believe in Jesus Christ chose a day to kill the believers if the sign had not happened."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.9"},"3 Nephi 1:9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p15"},"Nephi was sad because of the wickedness of those who did not believe in the Savior."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.10"},"3 Nephi 1:10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p17"},"Nephi prayed all day for the people who were going to be killed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.11-12"},"3 Nephi 1:11–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p19"},"The Lord comforted Nephi and told him that it would not get dark that night. Jesus would be born the next day in Bethlehem."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.13"},"3 Nephi 1:13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p21"},"That night the sun went down, but it did not get dark. The sign of Jesus Christ’s birth had come. The people were astonished."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.15"},"3 Nephi 1:15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p23"},"Those who had planned to kill the believers fell down and appeared to be dead."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.16"},"3 Nephi 1:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p25"},"They were afraid because they had been wicked. Now they knew that the Savior would be born and that the prophets had been right."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.17-18"},"3 Nephi 1:17–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p27"},"It stayed light all night. When the sun came up the next morning, the people knew that Jesus Christ would be born that day. The prophecies had been fulfilled."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.19-20"},"3 Nephi 1:19–20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p29"},"A new star appeared in the sky, just as the prophets had said it would."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.21"},"3 Nephi 1:21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p31"},"Satan still tried to get people not to believe the signs they had seen, but most did believe."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.22"},"3 Nephi 1:22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p33"},"Nephi and other Church leaders baptized all those who believed and repented."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.23"},"3 Nephi 1:23"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_044_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p35"},"There were glad tidings in the land because the words of the prophets had been fulfilled. Jesus Christ had been born."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-41-the-signs-of-christs-birth.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/1.26"},"3 Nephi 1:26"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
